@startuml AC-07_TOCTOU_Race_Condition

title AC-07 — TOCTOU Race Condition Drives Stock to Negative Quantity\nSTRIDE: Tampering | Severity: High | Mitigation: M-07

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Customer\n(Legitimate)" as customer #DDEEFF
actor "External Attacker\n(Concurrent Requests)" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Purchase Last Unit\nof a Product" as UC7 << normal >>
  usecase "Identify Slot with\nCurrentQuantity = 1" as AC7a << abuse >>
  usecase "Race Two Concurrent\nPurchases on Same Slot" as AC7 << abuse >>
  usecase "Drive CurrentQuantity\nto Negative Value" as AC7b << abuse >>
}

customer --> UC7

attacker --> AC7a
AC7a ..> AC7   : <<enables>>
AC7 ..> UC7    : <<threatens>>
AC7 ..> AC7b   : <<extends>>

note right of AC7
  **Preconditions:**
  • POST /sales checks stock and decrements
    in separate operations (no pessimistic lock)
  • @Transactional isolation: READ_COMMITTED
    (MySQL default) — two transactions each
    see pre-decrement stock level
  • Attacker can open two+ parallel HTTP
    connections with valid Customer JWTs
  • Target slot has CurrentQuantity = 1
end note

note right of AC7b
  **Impact:**
  Integrity: Slot.CurrentQuantity driven to -1,
  corrupting inventory model and restock logic
  Financial: two Sale records charged against
  one unit — one customer pays but receives nothing
  Availability: negative-inventory states block
  restocking workflows until manual correction
  Business: customer trust loss, operational
  overhead for fleet-wide reconciliation
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector:**
  T1: POST /sales {"machineId":"M-03","slotNumber":5} → reads qty=1, passes check
  T2: POST /sales {"machineId":"M-03","slotNumber":5} → reads qty=1, passes check
  T1 commits: qty=0  |  T2 commits: qty=-1 (invariant violation)
end note

@enduml
